      "content": {
        "title": "Bearing Surfaces and Implant Tribology — Core Principles",
        "definition": "Articulating material combinations in joint replacement and their wear characteristics, osteolysis potential, and clinical longevity.",
        "summary": "Metal-on-polyethylene, ceramic-on-ceramic, and highly cross-linked polyethylene reduce wear at different cost profiles. Trunnion corrosion affects metal-on-metal hips."
